    "G3_gap_20260410": "G3 fix in f84f950 is incomplete: next_token_inner recursively calls itself after consuming /* ... */ without skip_whitespace, so any block comment followed by whitespace (the realistic case) hits 'unexpected character'. Regression tests test_g3_block_comment_{basic,multiline,nested} were drafted in src/lexer.rs mod tests but removed after revealing the gap. Fix needed before ossification: add self.skip_whitespace() before the recursive call on line 346, or switch to self.next_token(). No real hexa source uses block comments today (only string literals match '/*'), so this has not been caught in the field."
  },
